 The code is a controller that extends the Controller class.

 It has an index() method, create() method, store() method, show() method, edit() method and destroy() method.

 The index(), create(), store(), show(), edit(), and destroy methods are public functions of the controller.

 The code is a controller for the BriefController class.

 The index() function returns a view that displays all of the briefs in the database.

 The create() function returns a view that displays when creating a new brief.

 The store() function creates and saves a new brief, returning redirecting to the index().

 The show($id) function displays an individual's specific brief with their ID.

 This will return to the index().

 This will also display edit and update functions for each individual's specific brief.

 These functions are called by using $id as an argument to these functions.

